  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a prospective, randomized vanguard trial of trauma patients admitted to the trauma
      surgery service at Intermountain Medical Center who are deemed to be at high risk for venous
      thromboembolism. Once identified and enrolled, subjects will be randomized to receive
      bilateral lower extremity duplex ultrasound surveillance versus no surveillance. The study
      will compare the two groups with regard to deep vein thrombosis, pulmonary embolism, and
      major and clinically relevant bleeding episode rates, both during the index hospitalization
      and at 90 days post-discharge.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
